The 38-year-old constable from Caledon in the Overberg region of the Western Cape was arrested on Friday in an undercover operation after the Grabouw dentist handed over R50 000.Hawks spokesman Captain Lloyd Ramovha said the cash was found in the handbag of the officer s 15-year-old niece who was also arrested. The off-duty constable allegedly approached (the dentist) purporting to be investigating instances of apparent false claims allegedly submitted to his medical aid by the dentist said Ramovha. He then demanded the money blackmailing the dentist in the process. The Hawks were alerted and an undercover operation was carried out leading to the swift arrest of the police officer and his niece outside the dentist s premises after the money was paid to him by the doctor. After the arrest the constable was admitted to hospital under police guard with symptoms of a heart attack. The teenager was released into her parents care.The pair will face corruption-related charges on Monday in the Grabouw Magistrate s Court.TMG Digital